==Details==
{{Quest details page|Mountain Daughter}}

==Walkthrough==
===Starting out===
[[File:Mountain Daughter - Map.png|thumb|300px|Map of the Mountain Camp.]]
{{Checklist|
*Head to the entrance of the mountain camp east of [[Rellekka]] or north of the {{Fairycode|ajr}} fairy ring.
*Take the path north, past the guard, and use your rope on a boulder you can push to get around.
*Head into the camp and talk to [[Hamal the Chieftain]]. {{Chat option|1Why is everyone being so hostile to me?|1So what are you doing up here?|1I will search for her!}}
}}
===Crisis===
{{Checklist|
*Dig some mud from the mud pond south of Hamal's house.
**If you do not have a staff, go north of Hamal's house and take a [[pole]]. Keep this throughout the quest.
*Go north, following the path along the lake westward.
*Use the mud on the tall tree then climb it. You do *not* need to do this again for subsequent climbs.
*Use your [[pole]] or staff on the clump of rocks to pole vault over.
*Use your [[plank]] on the flat stones. Keep this throughout the quest.
*Listen to the shining pool. {{Chat option|2Hello! Who are you?|2So what exactly do you want from me?|1That sounds like something I can do.|1I'll get right on it.}}
*Use your [[plank]] on the flat stone to return to shore.}}

===Making Peace===
''Note: Both tasks requested by [[Asleif]] (regarding Rellekka and finding a new food source) can be started at the same time. This reduces going back to the Mountain Camp multiple times.''{{Map|name=Svidi|x=2709|y=3692|r=14|mtype=square|align=right|caption=The area that Svidi roams within.}}
{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Hamal the Chieftain]] about the people of Rellekka. {{Chat option|2About the people of Rellekka... |1Why do you hate them so much?}}
*Search for [[Svidi]] between Rellekka and Keldagrim. {{Chat option|2Can't I persuade you to go in there somehow?}}
*Go to [[Rellekka]] and talk to [[Brundt the Chieftain]] in the longhall. {{Chat option|1Ask about the mountain camp.|1Did it contain vast magical powers?}} or {{Chat option|2Ask about the mountain camp.|1Did it contain vast magical powers?}} if [[Lunar Diplomacy]] started/completed.
*Return to the Mountain Camp, and enter the large tent south-west of Hamal the Chieftain.
*Use your [[pickaxe]] on the Ancient Rock located in the southern tent to get half a rock.
*Take this back to [[Rellekka]], and talk to Brundt the Chieftain {{Chat option|1Ask about the mountain camp.}}  or {{Chat option|2Ask about the mountain camp.}} if [[Lunar Diplomacy]] started/completed, who will give you the guarantee of safe passage.
*Take the guarantee to [[Svidi]]. You do not need to check on Svidi afterward.
*Return to [[Hamal the Chieftain]]. {{Chat option|2About the people of Rellekka...}}
}}

===The White Pearl===
{{Checklist|*Talk to Hamal the Chieftan again, this time about food supplies. {{Chat option|3About your food supplies...|1Never mind.}}
*Talk to [[Jokul]] just north of Hamal. He will tell you of a [[White Pearl]] plant that is very hardy.
*Travel to [[White Wolf Mountain]] ([[Keldagrim minecart system]] if [[The Giant Dwarf]] completed, or [[Gnome glider]] if [[The Grand Tree]] completed.)
*Equip [[gloves]] and pick-from the [[thorny bushes]] by the [[gnome glider]].
*Eat the [[white pearl]] you picked to get the [[white pearl seed]].
*Speak to [[Hamal the Chieftain]] to give him the white pearl seed. {{Chat option|2About your food supplies...}}
}}

===The Kendal===
Item required: Axe, Pole/Staff, Plank

Prepare to fight a level 70 creature that only uses melee.
{{Checklist|
*Speak to the shining pool again (remember to use the pole/staff and plank).
*Cross the gap back to shore without the plank, as this will put you closer to the cave.
*Follow the northern path east to a cave.
*Chop down the trees blocking your path (make sure you are facing east) 
*Enter the cave
*Talk to [[The Kendal]]. {{Chat option|1It's just me, no one special.|2You mean a sacrifice?|3You look like a man in a bearsuit!|2Can I see that corpse?|2I humbly request to be given the remains.|1I will kill you myself!}}
*Kill The Kendal. He can [[safespotted]] utilizing skeletons around the room.
*Take the [[corpse of woman]] 
*Return to Hamal the Chieftain. {{Chat option|1But he's not a god!|1I will.}}
*'''Gather 5 muddy rocks from around the camp.'''
*Talk to Ragnar near the tall tree by the lake to get Asleif's necklace. 
*Return to the shining pool and bury the corpse.
*Use the muddy rocks on the burial mound.(You make the mound by burying the corpse on the island.)
}}
'''Quest complete!'''

